For now, it's not a matter of what data to collect, but we need to ensure the instance discovery job runs against the host list to list all database instances.
I believe something is blocking the connection. We can't move forward until we get that job to run.

You can review these data again for the connection profile: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Solutions/Databases/Oracle/Recommended.htm#:~:text=host%20inventory%20results.-,Connection%20Profile,-The%20SQL%20Data<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Solutions/Databases/Oracle/Recommended.htm*:*:text=host*20inventory*20results.-,Connection*20Profile,-The*20SQL*20Data__;I34lJSUlJQ!!CiF3mHgEawk!B8bHaHRXy0ffhpxa8sV0OkyVTiggk2RAJEfGGYIXSy3xT6KgFOUajW8GhyZDjpoE4Vs3MJZl8b22VxKtUqcN5cntaw$>

Once the instance discovery runs successfully, you can run the Permission scan.
We need to review permission for the user and make sure traffic is not being blocked.
